    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single deficiency (Test conditions, achieved level 2 vs. required level 3) is accepted based on regulatory precedent establishing ASTM F1717 as the standard protocol and the availability of corroborating multi-laboratory experimental data. Comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification across all model inputs confirms that QoI prediction intervals encompass experimental observations. Overall credibility is judged sufficient to support a Medium assurance level for this Class II device submission.",
